Driving down West Charleston, I see one of those human "sign holders" waving a sign saying FRENCH BAKERY PASTRY BISTRO....I turn right, go past Flemming's and I arrive at Summerlin's first local pastry shop, Patisserie Manon(Named after their first-born daughter)  Chef/Owners Rachel and Jean-Paul Ladeyn have run two other successful locations(same name) in Tahiti and Moorea, French Polynesia before relocating to Nevada to open the Summerlin and Boulder City locations.
Kelly and Amanda(Hope I memorized/spelled your names right!
) were so nice and hospitable while I was in "Yelp" mode browsing the patisserie and snapping away with my camera to provide visuals for this review.
"Are you a Yelper?
" Kelly asks.
"Yes I am, It's time to promote another local business.
" I replied.
As you step inside, the sights and smells awaken your appetite...French pastries, artisan breads and assorted vienoiserie(danish, croissants), an open production area where "all the magic happens", a wall of assorted candies and truffles, and towards the back of the patisserie, all the savory bistro fare are displayed- savory pastries, sandwiches,  ham and cheese croissants, various types of quiche and pate, and today's specials, Lamb Ragout and Cassoulet.
Unfortunately at this time,being open for just over 7 weeks, they are only doing take-out, and are waiting for permits for the addition of tables and chairs, so patrons may enjoy dining in.
So I finally settlle for a savory item as well as a sweet item- I tried a Ham and Spinach Quiche, pretty rich and flavorful, and baked in either a puff pastry or filo dough crust and a Tart Tropizienne, a pastry consisting of Brioche with vanilla cream and peaches snadwiched in between which also tasted good and something different from what I usually see at work.
"Do you like Cassoulet?
(a hearty pork and white bean stew)" Kelly asked?
"Oh yeah, that's perfect for weather like this.
" I said.
She was nice enough to "hook it up'" along with peanut butter and raspberry macaroons, and sent me on my way.
Overall, a great first visit and I'll definitely be back.
Welcome to Nevada Rachel and Jean-Paul, and Thanks again Kelly and Amanda for your hospitality.....ALOHA!!

