The best french pastries - or any pastries really - in LV.
Seriously.
That place you're thinking of?
No.
I've been to my share of pastries around here, LA, SF, NYC, etc.
More importantly, I've been to Paris.
I know what it's supposed to be.
This is genuinely the only place that can come close to a proper baguette, almond croissant, and macaron.
As a matter of fact, this is the only place I've been to that knows an almond croissant isn't a croissant with almonds sprinkled on top, or that a baguette should have a hard shell and not have simple Wonderbread inside (like Lee's Sandwiches - the epitome of embracing a low standard and marketing it).
I am definitely judging this place on their desserts and not on their cafe side.
I don't have a lot of opinions on that half of the place.
It's just food.
I don't really know why you'd go there for that half anyway.
Go try this place if you haven't been there.
It has no equal in Las Vegas.

