I couldn't believe how good this little $2.95 sandwich could be and neither could she.
It was THAT GOOD!
So simple, yet insanely rich and flavorful.
The tart was delicious as well and made the perfect ending to the breakfast.
The coffee was refilled constantly while we stayed to chat well after the food was finished.
This kind of establishment is part of the reason I love this city.
You can go to an authentic French bakery and bask in the splendor of feeling like you're in another time and place, then pack up and head back to reality a five minute drive away.
